I didn't know OCaml had list comprehensions built-in:

$ ocaml camlp4oof.cma
        Objective Caml version 3.10.0

        Camlp4 Parsing version 3.10.0

# [x + 2*x + x/2 | x <- [1; 2; 3; 4]];;
- : int list = [3; 7; 10; 14]
#

